The paper proposes a novel 3D spatial representation for data fusion and scene reconstruction, which involves probabilistic modeling and efficient data structures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it discusses the use of sequential depth measurements for incremental refinement. The probabilistic modeling aspect of the paper also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the extraction of high-quality surfaces and reliable data fusion, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
